A pratdigger is late nineteenth and early twentieth century [[slang]] for a [[pickpocket]]. It relates to the action of stealing from a hip pocket.

In the early twenty first century the term was once again picked up by people on the streets of [[Britain]] and used to mean any sort of [[petty criminal]].

It has also come to mean either the sort of person who tends to bring along unpopular members of a social group to a social gathering, or to someone who seems to always have a rather obnoxious partner.


